Author: ANGUS
Vol / Page: 61
Edition:
Quote: On the treeless terraces of the Upper Clutha, the wagoners' campfires burned with such unusual fuels as 'buffalo chips' or dried dung, 'yellow pine' or straw and 'kaladdies' or flax stalks.
